Day 104 – SY0-701 Security+ Practice (FreeBrainDumps)
Completed questions 210–220 with comprehensive notes, definitions, and mistake review. Focused on web application attacks, system hardening, mobile security models, secure data destruction, risk calculations, and incident response procedures.

🔑 Topics Covered
🔐 System & Access Security

Firmware integrity checks

Ensures firmware has not been tampered with.

Helps detect low-level/rootkit compromises.

High-risk access monitoring

Systems analyze behavior patterns to detect anomalies and suspicious activity.

COPE (Corporate-Owned, Personally Enabled)

Company devices allow limited personal use.

Enforces encryption, remote wipe, and access controls.

🌐 Web & Application Security

Directory Traversal

Attackers attempt to access restricted directories/files outside intended paths.

SQL Injection

Malicious input manipulates database queries.

Can lead to unauthorized access, data leakage, or modification.

🛠️ Security Testing & Hardening

Sandbox Testing

Safe environment for analyzing suspicious code.

Limited visibility depending on configuration.

Server Hardening

First step before deployment:

Disable unnecessary services

Apply patches

Configure permissions

Reduce attack surface

💾 Data Protection

Secure Data Wiping

Overwrites data multiple times to prevent recovery.

Critical for decommissioning drives/devices.

📊 Risk Management

ALE (Annualized Loss Expectancy)

Formula:

ALE = SLE × ARO

Used to estimate yearly financial impact of risks.

Risk Acceptance

Chosen when:

System is critical

Mitigation is not feasible

Cost outweighs benefit

